  :synonyms ("Turing machine" "TURING MACHINE")
  :discipline (:cs-theory :math :logic)
  :kind (:model-of-computation :abstraction)
  :heritage-narrative "An abstract computational model consisting of a tape, a head, and a state; the standard theoretical model for what algorithms can compute; equivalent in power to the lambda calculus (Church-Turing thesis)."
